        🔹 1. What is MySQL?
                ✅ Answer
                
                MySQL is a Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) used to store data.
                
                💡 Explanation
                
                English: Stores data in tables (rows & columns)
                Tamil: 👉 MySQL என்பது data-ஐ table format-ல் store பண்ணும் database
                
                🔸 Example
                SELECT * FROM users;


        🔹 2. MySQL Trigger
                ✅ Answer
                
                Trigger is an auto-executing SQL query when event occurs.
                
                💡 Explanation
                
                English: Runs automatically on INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
                Tamil: 👉 Trigger → automatic ஆக run ஆகும் query
                
                🔸 Example
                CREATE TRIGGER log_user
                AFTER INSERT ON users
                FOR EACH ROW
                INSERT INTO logs VALUES (NOW());


        🔹 3. Primary Key vs Foreign Key vs Unique Key
                ✅ Answer
                Primary Key → unique + no null
                Foreign Key → relation
                Unique Key → no duplicate
                💡 Tamil
                
                👉 Primary → unique + null இல்லாது
                👉 Foreign → relation create பண்ணும்
                👉 Unique → duplicate இல்லாது
                
                🔸 Example
                PRIMARY KEY(id),
                FOREIGN KEY(user_id) REFERENCES users(id),
                UNIQUE(email)


        🔹 4. MySQL Index
                ✅ Answer
                
                Index improves query performance
                
                💡 Tamil
                
                👉 fast search செய்ய உதவும்
                
